# Canonical MinaGuard verification-key hash (decimal Field value).
#
# This is the hash MinaGuard.compile() produces from the CURRENT contracts/src
# when compiled for TESTNET (MINA_NETWORK_DOMAIN unset or != 'mainnet').
#
# The backend indexer filters on-chain zkApp events to this VK (via the
# MINAGUARD_VK_HASH env var) so it only records genuine MinaGuard vaults.
#
# IMPORTANT: mainnet and testnet produce DIFFERENT VKs because NETWORK_DOMAIN
# is a compile-time constant baked into the circuit (Field(1) for mainnet,
# Field(2) for testnet). A mainnet deployment requires a separate compile:
#
#     MINA_NETWORK_DOMAIN=mainnet bun run --filter contracts build && \
#     MINA_NETWORK_DOMAIN=mainnet bun run dev-helpers/cli.ts vk-hash compile
#
# Regenerate this file after ANY change under contracts/src:
#
#     bun run --filter contracts build && bun run dev-helpers/cli.ts vk-hash compile
#
# Consumers strip these comment lines and read the bare number below.
21242401101178794958609095315383522449210927189112915148880012896861832765572
